MANGO CHICKEN

Ingredients
-----------
2 lbs Chicken Thighs, trimmed, pricked
3 Mangoes, peeled, chunked
4 Tbsp Olive Oil
1 Tbsp Chili Powder
1 Tbsp Allspice, ground
1 Tbsp Cumin, ground
1 tsp Thyme, ground
1 tsp Pepper, black, ground
1 tsp Salt
1/4 Onion, large, white

Method
------
0. Put Mangoes, Onion and Olive Oil into Blendtec blender.
1. Add Spices: Chili Powder, Allspice, Cumin, Thyme, Black Pepper, and Salt.
2. Puree on "Whole Juice" setting. About 45 seconds, to get a thick liquid.
3. Pour over Chicken in casserole container or gallon size zip lock bag. 
4. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.
5. Place on Med-High heated grill. Brush or spoon extra marinade to cover chicken.
6. Flip when the edges are dry. Brush or spoon marinade to cover grilled side of chicken. 
7. Repeat set 6 at least two (2) more times, brushing marinade over the recently charred/grilled side.
8. Remove when Chicken is golden brown with some char on edges.

Notes
-----
You can substitue pork chops or pork tenderloin, too.